The President and senior White House officials met with organizations committed to passing bipartisan immigration reform. The leaders of these organizations expressed concerns about the separation of families caused by the broken immigration system. The President emphasized his concern for these families and asked the Secretary of Homeland Security to assess current practices and enforce immigration laws more humanely. The President also reiterated his commitment to pressuring Congressional Republicans to take action on immigration reform. The meeting included a list of participants, including government officials and representatives from various organizations.